<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-15T19:23:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-15T19:23:00-05:00" n="918" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d918">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7597</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Simpich</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nogales, Arizona</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-15T17:00:00-07:23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 15, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Telegraphic reports to Calles say family of John Lehr captured in
                            November by Yaquis has been rescued by General Martinez and will be
                            returned first opportunity to Lehr at Saqui Grande. District continues
                            quiet. Agents report Cananea and Ensanada orderly.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Simpich</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>